fields.name: VisualInspectionForDamage
fields.fieldText:
Visual Inspection for damage

Back plate

•Check for cracks in polycarbonate

•Check Webbing for cuts and frays

Hose Integrity

•Cuts and Nicks

Check Whistle

•Clean and unobstructed

Check contents gauge

•Clean and visible

Check Demand Valve (LDV)

•Is Low Pressure “O Ring” (Red) present?

Check Reducer Valve

•Is High Pressure “O Ring” (Black) present?

fields.name: MaskChecksDisply
fields.fieldText:
Mask Checks:

Visual inspection

•Rubber seals

•Demand valve attachment points

•Harness points

•Strap deformation

•Lenses cracks / crazing

Clean Mask use Wipes

•Removing ore-nasal

fields.name: PreparationDisplay
fields.fieldText:
Preparation:

Connect cylinder to back plate (Reducer Valve)

•Attach “Anti Rattle Strap” if non quick release cylinder

•Fasten cylinder strap (secure cylinder to backplate)

•Do not over tighten – can crack backplate

Attach Demand Valve to Mask

•Check Operation of “reset button”

Check Cylinder is filled

•Cylinder must be at least 80% full

fields.name: SystemTestsDisplay
fields.fieldText:
High Pressure Test (Hose Integrity)

•Pressurise System

•Turn cylinder valve off and observe contents gauge for 1 min

•Allowed to drop 10 bar permissible

Low Pressure Test

•Put kit on and pressurise system

•Don mask

•Observe Contents gauge and turn off Cylinder

•As hose empties - check whistle sounds (between 50 & 60 bar)

•As mask collapses, turn cylinder back on

•Loosen mask, activate “reset button” and remove mask
